  const id = this.route.snapshot.paramMap.get('id');
  console.log(id);
}
ğŸ‘‰ If URL is /user/10
ğŸ‘‰ Output will be 10
ğŸ¯ Interview Line:
ActivatedRoute is used to access route parameters, query parameters, and URL data in Angular.

Que 32) What is Route Guard?
------------------------------
Route Guard is used to control access to routes.
Only logged-in users can open dashboard.
If not logged in â†’ redirect to login page.
import { CanActivate } from '@angular/router';
export class AuthGuard implements CanActivate {
  canActivate(): boolean {
    return false; // block route
  }
}
Add in Routing:
{ 
  path: 'dashboard', 
  component: DashboardComponent,
  canActivate: [AuthGuard]
}
ğŸ‘‰ If true â†’ page opens
ğŸ‘‰ If false â†’ page blocked
Route Guard is used to protect routes and restrict access based on conditions like authentication.

Que 33) What is scope in Angular?
----------------------------------
In Angular, scope refers to the environment or context in which variables, expressions, and functions are evaluated. It
determines the visibility and accessibility of these variables within different parts of the application, particularly 
in relation to the component's template and controller.
Note: In Angular 2+ (modern Angular), the term scope is no longer used. It is replaced by component state and data binding.

Que 34) What type of DOM is used in Angular ?
------------------------------------------------
1ï¸âƒ£ Real DOM
Angular works with the Real DOM (the actual HTML structure in the browser).
When data changes, Angular updates the DOM.
But it does not refresh the full page like traditional websites.
2ï¸âƒ£ Change Detection
Angular uses a Change Detection mechanism.
It checks what data has changed.
Then it updates only that specific part of the page.
This makes the application fast and efficient.
ğŸ‘‰ Example:
If you change only the username, Angular updates only the username part, not the entire page.
3ï¸âƒ£ Shadow DOM (Optional Feature)
Angular can use Shadow DOM for component style isolation.
It keeps styles and behavior of one component separate from others.
This prevents CSS conflicts between components.
ğŸ‘‰ Example:
If two components use the same CSS class name, they will not affect each other when Shadow DOM is used.

Que 35) In how many ways can Bootstrap be embedded in Angular?
-------------------------------------------------------------
Bootstrap can be embedded in Angular in two main ways:
1ï¸âƒ£ Using NPM (Recommended Method)
Install Bootstrap using npm:
