  this.message = "Hello";
}, 2000);
After 2 seconds:
Value changes
NgZone detects it
Angular updates the UI automatically
Without NgZone, the UI might not update properly.
ğŸ”„ Real-Life Example
Think of NgZone like a manager in an office ğŸ‘¨â€ğŸ’¼
Employees (async tasks) are working.
When work finishes, they inform the manager.
Manager announces: â€œUpdate the display board!â€
NgZone = Manager
Async task = Employee
UI update = Display board update
ğŸ’¡ Extra (Important)
Sometimes we use:
this.ngZone.runOutsideAngular()
This tells Angular:
ğŸ‘‰ â€œDonâ€™t check for changes for this task.â€
This improves performance for heavy operations.
ğŸ“ In One Line
NgZone helps Angular detect async changes and update the UI automatically.

Que 45) How Do You Implement Authentication in Angular?
--------------------------------------------------------
Authentication means:
ğŸ‘‰ Checking if a user is logged in or not
ğŸ‘‰ Allowing access only to authorized users
In Angular, we usually use:
âœ… JWT Token,âœ… AuthGuard,âœ… Interceptor
ğŸªœ Step-by-Step Simple Flow
1ï¸âƒ£ User Login
User enters username & password.
