Que 52) What is Ivy in Angular?
-------------------------------
Ivy is Angularâ€™s new and improved rendering engine.
In simple words ğŸ‘‰
Ivy is the system inside Angular that converts your code into something the browser can understand and display.
ğŸ§  Why was Ivy introduced?
Older Angular versions were:
Slower to compile
Produced bigger application sizes
Harder to debug
Ivy was introduced to fix these problems.
âœ… What does Ivy improve?
Faster Compilation
Your app builds faster.
Smaller Bundle Size
Removes unused code (better tree-shaking).
Final app size becomes smaller.
Better Performance
Loads faster in the browser.
Better Debugging
Errors are clearer and easier to understand.
Easier Updates
Better backward compatibility.
ğŸ¯ Simple Example
Imagine you wrote 100 components, but you are using only 50.
ğŸ‘‰ Ivy automatically removes the unused 50 components from the final build.
Result: Smaller and faster application.
ğŸ“Œ In One Line
Ivy is Angularâ€™s modern rendering engine that makes applications faster, smaller, and easier to debug.

