Que 54) What is a Resolver in Angular?
-------------------------------------
A Resolver in Angular is used to load data before a page (route) opens.
In simple words ğŸ‘‰
A Resolver makes sure the required data is ready before the user sees the page.
ğŸ§  Why do we need it?
Normally:
User clicks a page
Page opens
Then API call runs
User sees loading spinner
With a Resolver:
User clicks a page
Angular loads the data first
Then the page opens with full data
So the user does not see an empty page or loading delay.
âœ… Example Situation
Imagine:
You open a User Details page
It needs user information from an API
Without Resolver:
Page opens first
Data loads later
With Resolver:
Data loads first
Then page opens with complete data
ğŸ¯ How it works (Simple Flow)
User clicks route
Resolver runs
Data is fetched
Route activates
Component gets ready data
ğŸ“Œ Simple Example
In routing:
{
  path: 'user/:id',
  component: UserComponent,
  resolve: { userData: UserResolver }
}
Angular will:
Call UserResolver
Wait for data
Then load UserComponent
ğŸ“Œ In One Line
A Resolver loads required data before a page opens, so the user sees a fully loaded page instead of a loading screen.

Que 55) What is the difference between Angular and React?
-----------------------------------------------------------
Both Angular and React are used to build web applications, but they are different in many ways.
ğŸ”¹ 1. What they are
Angular
A complete framework
Provides everything (routing, forms, HTTP, etc.) inside it
React
A library
Mainly used for building UI (User Interface)
You need extra libraries for routing, state management, etc.
ğŸ”¹ 2. Developed By
Angular â†’ Developed by Google
React â†’ Developed by Facebook (Meta)
ğŸ”¹ 3. Language Used
Angular â†’ Uses TypeScript (strongly typed)
React â†’ Uses JavaScript with JSX
ğŸ”¹ 4. Architecture
Angular â†’ Follows MVC / MVVM pattern
React â†’ Purely Component-based architecture
ğŸ”¹ 5. Best Used For
Angular
Large-scale applications
Enterprise projects
Complex business applications
React
Interactive UIs
Single Page Applications (SPA)
Fast and flexible frontend apps
ğŸ”¹ 6. Learning Curve
Angular â†’ Slightly harder (more concepts)
React â†’ Easier to start

Que 56) How are Angular expressions different from JavaScript expressions? 
--------------------------------------------------------------------------
Angular Expressions are used inside HTML templates for data binding.
They look like JavaScript, but they are simpler and safer.
JavaScript Expressions are used in .ts or .js files and can do almost anything.
ğŸ§  Where They Are Used
Angular Expressions â†’ Inside HTML template
Example:
{{ userName }}
{{ price + tax }}
JavaScript Expressions â†’ Inside TypeScript/JavaScript files
Example:
let total = price + tax;
ğŸ”¹ Main Differences
1ï¸âƒ£ Purpose
Angular expressions â†’ Used for displaying data in UI
JavaScript expressions â†’ Used for logic and calculations
2ï¸âƒ£ Restrictions
Angular expressions:
âŒ Cannot use loops (for, while)
âŒ Cannot use condition statements (if)
âŒ Cannot create new objects
âŒ Cannot access global variables like window, document
JavaScript expressions:
âœ… Can use all JavaScript features
3ï¸âƒ£ Security
Angular expressions are:
More secure
Restricted to avoid harmful code execution
ğŸ¯ Simple Example
Angular template:
{{ user.age + 5 }}
JavaScript file:
if (user.age > 18) {
  console.log("Adult");
}
ğŸ‘‰ Angular expression is simple and only for display.
ğŸ‘‰ JavaScript expression can control full program logic.
ğŸ“Œ In One Line
Angular expressions are simple, safe expressions used in templates for displaying data, while JavaScript expressions are more powerful and used for application logic.

