âœ… In one line:
Eager loading means loading all modules and features when the application starts, even if they are not immediately used.

Que 65) What is the purpose of Angularâ€™s Renderer2?
----------------------------------------------------
ğŸ‘‰ Renderer2 is used to safely change or update the DOM (HTML elements) in Angular.
In simple words:
Instead of directly using JavaScript like:
document.getElementById("myDiv").style.color = "red";
Angular recommends using Renderer2 to change elements safely.
ğŸ§  Why do we use Renderer2?
ğŸ”¹ 1. Platform Independent
It works in different environments like:
Browser
Server-side rendering (Angular Universal)
Web workers
So your app works properly everywhere.
ğŸ”¹ 2. More Secure
It helps prevent security issues like XSS attacks.
It handles DOM updates in a safer way.
ğŸ”¹ 3. Better Code Structure
It avoids direct DOM manipulation.
This makes code:
Cleaner,Easier to test, Easier to maintain
ğŸ”¹ 4. Consistent Behavior
It ensures your app behaves the same in different browsers and platforms.
ğŸ“Œ Simple Example
Instead of writing:
element.style.backgroundColor = 'blue';
Using Renderer2:
this.renderer.setStyle(element, 'background-color', 'blue');
ğŸ¯ In one line:
Renderer2 is a safe and Angular-friendly way to change HTML elements without directly touching the DOM.

Que 66) What are the benefits of using Web Workers in Angular?
--------------------------------------------------------------
ğŸ‘‰ Web Workers allow Angular to run heavy tasks in the background without freezing the UI.
ğŸ§  Simple Meaning
Normally, Angular runs everything on the main thread (UI thread).
If you do heavy work like:
Large calculations
Processing big data
Complex loops
ğŸ‘‰ The screen may freeze or become slow.
Web Workers solve this problem by running heavy tasks in the background.
ğŸ¯ Benefits in Simple Words
ğŸ”¹ 1. Improved Performance
Heavy work runs in the background.
The main screen stays smooth and fast.
ğŸ”¹ 2. Better User Experience
The app does not freeze while doing complex operations.
Users can still click buttons and scroll normally.
ğŸ”¹ 3. Parallel Processing
Tasks can run separately from the main thread.
This makes big operations faster.
ğŸ”¹ 4. Better Scalability
When the app handles large data or high load, Web Workers help manage it efficiently.
ğŸ“Œ Example
Imagine:
You are uploading and processing a large file.
Without Web Worker â†’ App becomes slow.
With Web Worker â†’ Processing happens in background, UI remains responsive.
âœ… In one line:
Web Workers help run heavy tasks in the background so the Angular app stays fast and responsive.

Que 67) What are Impure Pipes in Angular?
------------------------------------------
ğŸ‘‰ Impure pipes are pipes that run every time Angular checks for changes.
ğŸ§  Simple Meaning
Normally, Angular pipes (pure pipes) run only when the input value changes.
But impure pipes run:
Every time change detection runs
Even if the input value has not changed
ğŸ“Œ Example
Imagine you have an array:
items = ['Apple', 'Banana'];
If you push a new item:
items.push('Mango');
A pure pipe may not detect this change.
But an impure pipe will detect it and update the result.
âš ï¸ Important
Because impure pipes run very often:
They can slow down the application
They may affect performance
So they should be used carefully.
ğŸ”¹ Difference in Simple Words
Pure Pipe â†’ Runs only when input changes
Impure Pipe â†’ Runs on every change detection cycle
ğŸ¯ In one line:
Impure pipes are pipes that run every time Angular checks for changes, even if the input value has not changed.

Que 68) What are Pure Pipes in Angular?
----------------------------------------
ğŸ‘‰ Pure pipes are pipes that run only when the input value changes.
ğŸ§  Simple Meaning
If the data does not change â†’
The pipe will not run again.
If the data changes â†’
The pipe will run and update the result.
ğŸ“Œ Example
name = "Mahesh";
If the name stays the same â†’ pipe does not run again.
If the name changes to "Rahul" â†’ pipe runs and updates the output.
ğŸ¯ Why are pure pipes better?
Faster performance
More efficient
Run only when needed
Thatâ€™s why pure pipes are default in Angular.
ğŸ”¹ Simple Comparison
Pure Pipe â†’ Runs only when input changes (efficient)
Impure Pipe â†’ Runs every time change detection runs (less efficient)
âœ… In one line:
Pure pipes are pipes that re-run only when their input value changes, making them efficient and faster.

Que 69) What is PipeTransform Interface in Angular?
----------------------------------------------------
ğŸ‘‰ PipeTransform is an interface used when creating a custom pipe in Angular.
ğŸ§  Simple Meaning
When you create your own pipe, Angular expects you to implement a method called:
transform()
The PipeTransform interface ensures that your pipe has this transform() method.
ğŸ“Œ Why is it needed?
It tells Angular:
ğŸ‘‰ â€œThis class is a pipe and it will transform data.â€
ğŸ”¹ Simple Example
import { Pipe, PipeTransform } from '@angular/core';
@Pipe({
  name: 'uppercaseCustom'
})
export class UppercaseCustomPipe implements PipeTransform {
  transform(value: string): string {
    return value.toUpperCase();
  }
}
Here:
PipeTransform makes sure we implement the transform() method.
transform() changes the input value.
ğŸ¯ What does transform() do?
It:
Takes input value
Modifies it
Returns the updated value
âœ… In one line:
PipeTransform is an interface that ensures a custom pipe has a transform() method to modify data.








